comment: There is no "surprise" in a for-all with implication if there exists a value where the antecedent is true. This is one way to prevent for-all with implication from allowing anything. For a contrast, see ~ alimp-surprise . The allsome quantifier also counters this problem, see ~ df-alsi . (Contributed by David A. Wheeler, 27-Oct-2018.)
